items.name: Paneer Chilly
items.description: [Jain Food] Paneer Chilli is an Indo-Chinese delight featuring succulent cubes of paneer marinated in a spicy blend of ginger, garlic, and soy sauce, then fried to golden perfection

items.name: Exotic Mexican Combo

items.name: Dal Makhani
items.description: Dal Makhani is a rich and creamy North Indian lentil curry made with black lentils, kidney beans, butter, cream, and a blend of spices. It's simmered for hours to create a velvety texture and served with rice or Indian breads.

items.name: Veg Toofani
items.description: [Also Available in Jain] Veg Toofani is a colorful and spicy vegetarian dish from Indian cuisine, featuring a variety of vegetables cooked in a tangy tomato-based sauce with aromatic spices.

items.name: Mix Veg
items.description: [Also Available in Jain]  Mix veg is a flavorful Indian dish made by cooking a variety of vegetables with aromatic spices until tender. It's versatile, colorful, and often customized to personal taste preferences.

items.name: Veg Kolhapuri
items.description: [Also Available in Jain] Veg Kolhapuri is a spicy Maharashtrian vegetarian dish with a mix of vegetables cooked in a fiery tomato-based sauce, enriched with aromatic spices like cloves, cinnamon, and cumin seeds.

items.name: Veg Kofta
items.description: Veg Kofta is a vegetarian dish consisting of deep-fried vegetable balls served in a flavorful gravy. The koftas are made from mashed vegetables and spices, while the gravy is rich with onions, tomatoes, and spices. It's often enjoyed with rice or Indian breads.

items.name: Veg kheema in Hari Do Pyaza
items.description: Veg Kheema in Hari do Pyaz is a vegetarian dish featuring a minced vegetable mixture cooked with green onions (hari pyaz) and spices

items.name: Subz Reshmi
items.description: Subz Reshmi is a creamy vegetarian dish featuring a medley of vegetables cooked in a rich sauce made from cashews, cream, and yogurt, seasoned with aromatic spices. It's served hot with Indian breads or rice and is known for its luxurious texture and indulgent flavor.

items.name: Malai Kofta
items.description: [Also Available in Jain] Malai Kofta is a luxurious Indian dish featuring creamy, fried dumplings (koftas) served in a rich, mildly spiced tomato-based sauce. It's garnished with nuts and cream, served with bread or rice.

items.name: Diwani Handi
items.description: Diwani Handi is a sumptuous Indian dish featuring a medley of vegetables cooked in a creamy tomato-based sauce, infused with a blend of aromatic spices. It's a flavorful delight often enjoyed with your choice of bread or rice.

items.name: Paneer Tikka Masala
items.description: [Also Available in Jain]Paneer Tikka Masala is a beloved Indian dish with grilled paneer cubes in a creamy tomato-based sauce, infused with aromatic spices. It's a flavorful favorite, enjoyed with bread or rice.

items.name: Kaju Curry
items.description: [Also Available in Jain] Kaju Curry, also known as Cashew Curry, is a rich and flavorful Indian dish that features whole cashews cooked in a creamy, spiced gravy. This dish is known for its luxurious texture and delightful taste, making it a popular choice for special occasions and festive meals.

items.name: Paneer Pasanda
items.description: [Jain Food]  Paneer Pasanda is cherished for its creamy texture, bold flavors, and the combination of tender stuffed paneer with a luscious gravy, making it a favorite among paneer lovers in Indian cuisine.

items.name: Paneer Butter Masala
items.description: Also available in Jain. Paneer butter masala is a quintessential Indian dish, where succulent cubes of paneer are enveloped in a luscious tomato based gravy, enriched with creamy butter and aromatic spices.

items.name: Paneer Cube Kadhai
items.description: Paneer Cube Kadai is a flavorful North Indian dish featuring tender cubes of paneer cooked with an aromatic blend of spices and vibrant bell peppers

items.name: Paneer Lababdar
items.description:
[Also Available in Jain] 
Paneer Lababdar is a culinary masterpiece, where succulent cubes of paneer luxuriate in a creamy tomato-based gravy, kissed with aromatic spices and enriched with butter and cream.

items.name: Cheese Begam Bahar
items.description:
[Also Available in Jain] 
Cheese Begum Bahar is a regal delicacy, where succulent cubes of cheese are adorned in a velvety gravy, marrying the richness of cream and butter with the warmth of aromatic spices

items.name: Paneer Makhamali
items.description: Paneer Makhmali epitomizes culinary sophistication, where each succulent cube of paneer is enveloped in a velvety symphony of flavors.

items.name: Dal Fry
items.description: [Also Available in Jain]  Dal Fry is a comforting Indian dish made with boiled lentils cooked with onions, tomatoes, and spices. It's garnished with fresh cilantro and often served with rice or Indian breads.

items.name: Dal Tadka
items.description:
[Also Available in Jain] 
Dal Tadka is a flavorful Indian dish made with creamy lentils tempered with aromatic spices like cumin, mustard seeds, and dried red chilies.

items.name: Schezwan Noodles
items.description: Schezwan noodles are a spicy and flavorful Chinese Indian fusion dish. They feature stir fried noodles tossed with a variety of vegetables in a bold schezwan sauce.

items.description: [Jain Food]

items.name: Dum Biryani
items.description: Dum biryani is a veg version of the traditional biryani made with a flavorful mixed of vegetables, fragrant basmati rice and a blend of spices.

items.name: Hyderabadi Biryani
items.description: This aromatic and flavorful biryani features a tantalizing blend of fragrant basmati rice, assorted vegetables and a medley of spices.

items.name: Jeera Rice
items.description: Very versatile plate of the basmati rice sauteed in roasted cumin seeds. goes well with all our dals and gravies.

items.name: Khichdi
items.description: LEVEL 5 Special Khichdi is a comforting Indian one dish made with rice, lentils, and spices. It's hearty, nourishing, and easy to prepare. Rice and lentils are cooked together with aromatic spices until tender, creating a creamy and flavorful dish. Enjoyed hot, it's often garnished with fresh coriander leaves and served with yogurt or pickle. Perfect for a quick weeknight meal or as a comforting dish any time of the year.

items.name: Roti
items.description: Plain roti is a traditional Indian flatbread made from whole wheat flour dough. It's rolled thin, cooked on a hot skillet until it puffs up and served hot with ghee or butter. It has a soft, chewy texture and a mild, nutty flavor.

items.name: Laccha Paratha
items.description: Laccha paratha is an Indian flatbread known for its flaky, layered texture. Made from whole wheat flour, it's layered with ghee or oil, coiled, flattened and cooked until golden brown.

items.name: Butter Naan
items.description: Butter naan is a soft Indian flatbread made from refined flour dough, cooked until golden brown and brushed with butter or ghee. It pairs perfectly with North Indian dishes, offering a rich, buttery flavor and a fluffy texture.

items.name: Methi Laccha Paratha
items.description: Methi laccha paratha is a layered Indian flatbread infused with fresh fenugreek [methi] leaves. Made from whole wheat flour, it's layered with ghee or oil and coiled to create a flaky texture, then cooked until golden brown.

items.name: Garlic Naan
items.description: Garlic naan is a type of Indian flatbread made from a leavened dough with minced garlic. It's traditionally baked in a tandoor, resulting in a soft, chewy texture with a crispy exterior.

items.name: Cheesee Kulcha
items.description: Cheese kulcha is a North Indian flatbread made from refined flour dough stuffed with a spiced cheese mixture. The dough is rolled out, stuffed with grated cheese, green chilies, coriander and spices, then cooked in a tandoor or on a skillet until golden and puffed. It’s served hot, often brushed with butter and pairs well with dishes like chole or dal makhani. It has a crisp outer layer and a soft, cheesy interior.

items.name: Hot and Sour Veg Soup
items.description: [Jain food] Hot and Sour Soup is a popular Chinese soup known for its spicy, tangy, and flavorful broth

items.name: Manchow Soup
items.description:
[Jain food] 
Manchow Soup: A hearty Indo-Chinese broth brimming with vegetables and seasoned with garlic, ginger, soy sauce, and chili paste. Topped with crispy fried noodles and garnished with green onions, it's a flavorful delight served hot as an appetizer.

items.name: Sweet Lassi
items.description: Sweet lassi is a creamy and refreshing indian yogurt-based drink. It's made by blending yogurt with water or milk, sweetening it with sugar or honey, and optionally adding cardamom or saffron. Served chilled, it has a sweet and tangy flavor, perfect as a refreshing beverage alongside spicy Indian dishes.

items.name: Masala Buttermilk
items.description: Masala chaas is a spiced Indian buttermilk beverage made by blending yogurt with water and adding roasted cumin powder, black salt, chaat masala and fresh coriander. It's chilled and served cold, offering a tangy, savory and refreshing taste.
